For the chicken:
• 1 kg (2.2 lbs) chicken wings (mid-joints or drumettes, or a mix)
• 1 teaspoon salt
• ½ teaspoon ground black pepper
• 1 teaspoon garlic powder (optional, for extra flavor)
• 2 tablespoons fish sauce (preferably Vietnamese, like Red Boat or Three Crabs)
• 1 tablespoon sugar
• 1 tablespoon lime juice (or rice vinegar)
• 3 cloves garlic, finely minced
• 1 small shallot, finely minced (or ¼ red onion)
• 1-2 bird’s eye chilies, finely chopped (optional)

For frying:
• 1 cup cornstarch (or potato starch)
• ½ cup all-purpose flour
• Neutral oil for deep frying

For the fish sauce glaze:
• 4 tablespoons fish sauce
• 4 tablespoons sugar
• 2 tablespoons water
• 2 tablespoons lime juice
• 2 cloves garlic, finely minced
• 1-2 bird’s eye chilies

Garnish (optional):
• Chopped cilantro
• Fried garlic bits
• Lime wedges";

data.name: guna2HtmlLabel15.Text
data.value:
Step-by-Step Instructions

1. Marinate the Chicken (30 minutes – overnight)

Rinse chicken wings under cold water and pat completely dry with paper towels (dry wings = crispy skin).
In a large bowl, combine:
- 2 tbsp fish sauce
- 1 tbsp sugar
- 1 tbsp lime juice
- Minced garlic, shallot, chilies
- Salt, black pepper, garlic powder

Add chicken wings and massage marinade into every crevice.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes (best: 2–4 hours or overnight).

2. Prepare the Fish Sauce Glaze

In a small saucepan, combine:
- 4 tbsp fish sauce
- 4 tbsp sugar
- 2 tbsp water
- 2 tbsp lime juice

Bring to a gentle simmer over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves (~1 minute).
Add minced garlic and chilies. Taste and adjust (more lime for sour, more sugar for sweet).
Optional: Stir in cornstarch slurry and cook 30 seconds until slightly thickened. Set aside.

3. Coat the Wings

Remove wings from marinade and let excess drip off (do not rinse).
In a large bowl or zip-lock bag, mix 1 cup cornstarch + ½ cup flour (optional).
Toss wings in the dry coating until evenly and lightly dusted (shake off excess).

4. Double-Fry for Maximum Crispiness

Heat oil in a deep pot or wok to 325°F (160°C).
Fry wings in batches (don’t overcrowd) for 5–6 minutes until pale golden. Remove and drain.
Increase oil temperature to 375°F (190°C).
Fry wings again for 3–4 minutes until deep golden and ultra-crispy. Drain well.

5. Toss in Glaze

While wings are hot, return the glaze to low heat to warm.
Add half the glaze into a large clean bowl.
Toss in hot wings immediately and coat evenly. Add more glaze gradually until glossy.

6. Serve

Plate immediately on a bed of lettuce or cucumber slices.
Garnish with cilantro, fried garlic, and lime wedges.
Serve with steamed rice or as an appetizer with cold beer.

Pro Tips
- Crispiest results: Double-fry + cornstarch + dry wings.
- Make-ahead: Fry once, cool, refrigerate. Re-fry at 375°F for 3 minutes before glazing.
- Vegetarian version: Substitute wings with tofu or cauliflower.
- Spice level: Remove chili seeds for milder heat.

Enjoy your sticky, garlicky, umami-packed Canh Ga Chien Nuoc Mam! "
